  <static seed="9" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/PolynomialMultiplication/PolynomialMultiplication5.pg">
    <statement><p>Multiply the polynomials.</p>
<p><m>{10x}\left({6x-9}\right)=</m><fillin characters="16" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>60x^{2}-90x</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>We multiply the monomial by each term in the binomial, using 
the properties of exponents to help us.  <me>\begin{aligned}
              {10x}({6x-9})\amp ={60x^{2}-90x}
      \end{aligned}</me></p>
</solution>
